Context: George Brown College has more than 35 years of experience in providing English as a Second Language (ESL) programming. The college has articulation agreements with various language schools in Toronto and across Canada. Some of the institutions the college has built partnerships with are not named in the text. The college is committed to producing graduates prepared for the international workplace and advancing an intercultural perspective. George Brown College can be contacted at 416-415-2000 or TTY: 1-877-515-5559, or by emailing ask.george@georgebrown.ca. The college has a social media hub that can be visited. The information contained in the website is subject to change without notice and should not be viewed as a representation, offer or warranty. Students are responsible for verifying George Brown College fee requirements.
